The Chronicle Celebrating Bulawayo’s finest in artistic excellence. . . The most glamorous awards ceremony in the city, the Roil Bulawayo Arts Awards (RoilBAAs) was held at the Large City Hall on Christmas Eve, a move which was meant to lighten up the festive season and also accommodate diasporans who were in the country. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-672926" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/Untitled-3-copy-1-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/Untitled-3-copy-1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/Untitled-3-copy-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-672929" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/Untitled-4-copy-1-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/Untitled-4-copy-1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/Untitled-4-copy-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Like always, the red-carpet affair was on fire as people went all out to dress for the occasion. The performances and presentations on stage confirmed that RoilBAAs is one of the best organised awards not only in Bulawayo but in the country. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-672935" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/Untitled-2-copy-1-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/Untitled-2-copy-1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/Untitled-2-copy-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The awards whose vision and objective is to change artistes’ lives, saw the People”s Choice Award winner Msiz’Kay being presented with a serviced residential stand. <im